{
  "id": "api/http/testing/MockConnection",
  "title": "MockConnection",
  "contents": "<article>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 class=\"no-toc\" id=\"mockconnection\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockconnection\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>MockConnection</h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label class\">class</label>\n    <label class=\"api-status-label deprecated\">deprecated</label>\n    \n    \n    <span class=\"version\"></span>\n  </header>\n\n  \n  <!-- INFO BAR -->\n<section class=\"info-bar\">\n\n<table class=\"is-full-width\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n  <th>npm Package</th>\n  <td><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@angular/http\">@angular/http</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <th>Module</th>\n  <td><code>import { <a href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection\" class=\"code-anchor\">MockConnection</a> } from <a href=\"api/http/testing\">'@angular/http/testing'</a>;</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n  <th>Source</th>\n  <td><a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/5.2.11/packages/http/testing/src/mock_backend.ts#L14-L106\">http/testing/src/mock_backend.ts</a></td>\n</tr>\n\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n  \n  \n  \n<section class=\"deprecated\">\n  <h2 id=\"deprecation-notes\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#deprecation-notes\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Deprecation Notes</h2>\n  <p>use @angular/common/http instead</p>\n\n</section>\n\n  <section class=\"class-overview\">\n<h2 id=\"overview\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#overview\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Overview</h2>\n<code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\">\nclass <a href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection\" class=\"code-anchor\">MockConnection</a> implements <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/Connection\">Connection</a> {\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#constructor()\">constructor(req: Request)</a>\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#readyState\">readyState: ReadyState</a>\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#request\">request: Request</a>\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#response\">response: ReplaySubject&#x3C;Response></a>\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockRespond\">mockRespond(res: Response)</a>\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockDownload\">mockDownload(res: Response)</a>\n  <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockError\">mockError(err?: Error)</a>\n}\n</code-example>\n</section>\n\n  \n\n  \n\n\n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Description</h2>\n  <p>Mock Connection to represent a <a href=\"api/http/Connection\"><code>Connection</code></a> for tests.</p>\n\n</section>\n\n\n  \n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n<section class=\"constructors\">\n  <h2 id=\"constructor\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#constructor\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Constructor</h2>\n  \n    <div class=\"constructor\">\n  <a id=\"constructor()\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">constructor(req: <a href=\"api/http/Request\" class=\"code-anchor\">Request</a>)</code-example></div>\n\n    \n    \n  \n</section>\n\n\n\n\n<section class=\"instance-members\">\n  <h2 id=\"members\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#members\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Members</h2>\n  \n    <div class=\"instance-member\">\n  <a id=\"readyState\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">readyState: <a href=\"api/http/ReadyState\" class=\"code-anchor\">ReadyState</a></code-example>\n  <p>Describes the state of the connection, based on <code>XMLHttpRequest.readyState</code>, but with\nadditional states. For example, state 5 indicates an aborted connection.</p>\n\n  </div>\n\n    \n    <hr class=\"hr-margin\">\n  \n    <div class=\"instance-member\">\n  <a id=\"request\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">request: <a href=\"api/http/Request\" class=\"code-anchor\">Request</a></code-example>\n  <a href=\"api/http/Request\"><code>Request</code></a>\n<p> instance used to create the connection.</p>\n\n  </div>\n\n    \n    <hr class=\"hr-margin\">\n  \n    <div class=\"instance-member\">\n  <a id=\"response\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">response: ReplaySubject&#x3C;<a href=\"api/http/Response\" class=\"code-anchor\">Response</a>></code-example>\n  <a href=\"api/core/EventEmitter\"><code>EventEmitter</code></a>\n<p> of <a href=\"api/http/Response\"><code>Response</code></a>. Can be subscribed to in order to be notified when a\nresponse is available.</p>\n\n  </div>\n\n    \n    <hr class=\"hr-margin\">\n  \n    <div class=\"instance-member\">\n  <a id=\"mockRespond\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">mockRespond(res: <a href=\"api/http/Response\" class=\"code-anchor\">Response</a>)</code-example>\n  <p>Sends a mock response to the connection. This response is the value that is emitted to the\n<a href=\"api/core/EventEmitter\"><code>EventEmitter</code></a> returned by <a href=\"api/http/Http\"><code>Http</code></a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"example\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#example\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Example</h3>\n<code-example>\nvar connection;\nbackend.connections.subscribe(c => connection = c);\nhttp.request('data.json').subscribe(res => console.log(res.text()));\nconnection.mockRespond(new <a href=\"api/http/Response\" class=\"code-anchor\">Response</a>(new <a href=\"api/http/ResponseOptions\" class=\"code-anchor\">ResponseOptions</a>({ body: 'fake response' }))); //logs\n'fake response'\n</code-example>\n\n  </div>\n\n    \n    <hr class=\"hr-margin\">\n  \n    <div class=\"instance-member\">\n  <a id=\"mockDownload\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">mockDownload(res: <a href=\"api/http/Response\" class=\"code-anchor\">Response</a>)</code-example>\n  <p>Not yet implemented!</p>\n<p>Sends the provided <a href=\"api/http/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> to the <code>downloadObserver</code> of the <code><a href=\"api/http/Request\" class=\"code-anchor\">Request</a></code>\nassociated with this connection.</p>\n\n  </div>\n\n    \n    <hr class=\"hr-margin\">\n  \n    <div class=\"instance-member\">\n  <a id=\"mockError\"></a>\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\">mockError(err?: Error)</code-example>\n  <p>Emits the provided error object as an error to the <a href=\"api/http/Response\"><code>Response</code></a> <a href=\"api/core/EventEmitter\"><code>EventEmitter</code></a>\nreturned\nfrom <a href=\"api/http/Http\"><code>Http</code></a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"example-1\"><a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/http/testing/MockConnection#example-1\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a>Example</h3>\n<code-example>\nvar connection;\nbackend.connections.subscribe(c => connection = c);\nhttp.request('data.json').subscribe(res => res, err => console.log(err)));\nconnection.mockError(new Error('error'));\n</code-example>\n\n  </div>\n\n    \n    \n  \n</section>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</section></article>\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/http/Connection\n - api/http/XHRConnection\n - api/http/testing\n - api/http/testing/MockBackend\n - guide/upgrade\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/core/EventEmitter\n - api/http/Connection\n - api/http/Http\n - api/http/ReadyState\n - api/http/Request\n - api/http/Response\n - api/http/ResponseOptions\n - api/http/testing\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#constructor\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#constructor()\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#deprecation-notes\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#description\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#example\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#example-1\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#members\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockDownload\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockError\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockRespond\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#mockconnection\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#overview\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#readyState\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#request\n - api/http/testing/MockConnection#response\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/5.2.11/packages/http/testing/src/mock_backend.ts#L14-L106\n - https://www.npmjs.com/package/@angular/http\n-->"
}